@node GMap FSet Result Types
@subsection GMap FSet Result Types

@deffn {GMap result type} set @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns a CHAMP set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-set @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a CHAMP set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  @var{compare-fn-name} can
be supplied to specify a custom organization.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-set @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a WB-set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  @var{compare-fn-name} can be
supplied to specify a custom ordering.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} union @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns the union of the sets (or bags), optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} intersection @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns the intersection of the sets (or bags), optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  (If zero sets
are supplied, returns the full set; see @href{Function full-set, @code{full-set}}.)
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} map @ @r{&key} filter @r{(}default @r{@code{nil})} no-default?
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.  If @var{default} is supplied, that will be the map's @href{Map
and Seq Defaults, default}; if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no default.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-map @ @r{&key} filter @r{(@var{default} @code{nil})} no-default? key-compare-fn-name val-compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.  @var{default} will be the map's @href{Map and Seq Defaults,
default}; but if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no default.  @var{key-compare-fn-name} and
@var{val-compare-fn-name}, if supplied, must be symbols naming the comparison functions to be used
for keys and values respectively (these default to @code{compare}).
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-map @ @r{&key} filter @r{(@var{default} @code{nil})} no-default? key-compare-fn-name val-compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.  @var{default} will be the map's @href{Map and Seq Defaults,
default}; but if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no default.  @var{key-compare-fn-name} and
@var{val-compare-fn-name}, if supplied, must be symbols naming the comparison functions to be used
for keys and values respectively (these default to @code{compare}).
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} map-union @r{&key @var{val-fn} (@var{default} @code{nil})} filterp
Returns the @href{Method map-union (map map), map-union} of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  If
@var{val-fn} is supplied, it is passed to @code{map-union}.  @var{default} will be the map's
@href{Map and Seq Defaults, default}; but if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no
default.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} map-intersection @r{&key @var{val-fn} (@var{default} @code{nil})} filterp
Returns the @href{Method map-intersection (map map), map-intersection} of the values, optionally filtered by
@var{filterp}.  If @var{val-fn} is supplied, it is passed to @code{map-intersection}.  @var{default}
will be the map's @href{Map and Seq Defaults, default}; but if @var{no-default?} is true, the map
will have no default.  If zero maps are intersected, returns @code{nil} (there's no identity value
for this operation).
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} map-to-sets @ @r{&key} filterp key-compare-fn-name val-compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function.  Returns a map from the first values, with each one
mapped to a set of the corresponding second values.  If you supply @var{val-compare-fn-name}, to
customize the organization of the range sets, the returned map will use @code{eql-compare} as its
@var{val-compare-fn}.  Also, @var{filterp}, if supplied, must take two arguments.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} bag @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns a CHAMP bag of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-bag @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a CHAMP bag of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  @var{compare-fn-name} can
be supplied to specify a custom organization.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-bag @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a WB-bag of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  @var{compare-fn-name} can be
supplied to specify a custom ordering.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} bag-pairs @ @r{&key} filterp
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a bag of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-bag-pairs @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP bag of the pairs, optionally filtered
by @var{filterp}.  @var{filterp}, if supplied, must take two arguments.  @var{compare-fn-name} can
be supplied to specify a custom organization.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-bag-pairs @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a WB-bag of the values, optionally filtered by
@var{filterp}.  @var{filterp}, if supplied, must take two arguments.  @var{compare-fn-name} can be
supplied to specify a custom ordering.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} bag-sum @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns the bag-sum of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} bag-product @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns the bag-product of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.  (If zero bags are
supplied, returns the full set, which contains every value with multiplicity 1; see @href{Function
full-set, @code{full-set}}.)
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} seq @ @r{&key} filterp
@deffnx {GMap result type} wb-seq @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns a seq of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} concat @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns the concatenation of the seq values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} tuple @ @r{&key} filterp
@deffnx {GMap result type} dyn-tuple @ @r{&key} filterp
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a dynamic tuple of the pairs.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} replay-set @ @r{&key} filterp
Returns a CHAMP replay-set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-replay-set @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a CHAMP replay-set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@var{compare-fn-name} can be supplied to specify a custom organization.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-replay-set @ @r{&key} filterp compare-fn-name
Returns a WB-tree replay-set of the values, optionally filtered by @var{filterp}.
@var{compare-fn-name} can be supplied to specify a custom ordering.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} replay-map @ @r{&key} filter @r{@var{default} @code{nil})} no-default? key-compare-fn-name val-compare-fn-name
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.  If @var{default} is supplied, that will be the map's @href{Map
and Seq Defaults, default}; if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no default.
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} ch-replay-map @ @r{&key} filter @r{@var{default} @code{nil})} no-default?
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a CHAMP map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
supplied, must take two arguments.  If @var{default} is supplied, that will be the map's @href{Map
and Seq Defaults, default}; if @var{no-default?} is true, the map will have no default.
@var{key-compare-fn-name} and @var{val-compare-fn-name}, if supplied, must be symbols naming the
comparison functions to be used for keys and values respectively (these default to @code{compare}).
@end deffn

@deffn {GMap result type} wb-replay-map @ @r{&key} filter @r{@var{default} @code{nil})} no-default?
Consumes two values from the mapped function; returns a WB-tree map of the pairs.  @var{filterp}, if
